Paper Mario mods are built with [Paper Mario DX](https://github.com/bates64/papermario-dx), a modding-focused version
of the game's [decompilation](https://papermar.io). You copy the code, make your changes, and compile a new ROM.

Because you're working in the actual source code, you can change *anything* - new maps, new items, new battle mechanics,
or things nobody's thought of yet. Many mods can be made just by replacing assets like sprite, textures, and music.
Changing game logic requries some C.

## Requirements

You will need:

- A computer running Windows 10+, macOS, or Linux
- The [Paper Mario (US) ROM](https://dumping.guide/carts/nintendo/n64#methods) in [.z64](https://hack64.net/tools/swapper.php) format
- [Visual Studio Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/) (or a different editor)

## Installation

{% tabs %}
{% tabitem label="Windows" %}
  {% steps %}
  1. Open PowerShell in administrator mode by right-clicking and selecting "Run as administrator".
  2. Type `wsl --install` and press Enter.
  3. Restart your computer.
  4. After restarting, an "Ubuntu" installation window will appear. Follow the instructions to set it up.
  5. Open Ubuntu, type `bash <(curl -Ls https://bates64.com/setup-dx.sh)`, and press enter.
  6. Follow the instructions in the Ubuntu window.
  {% /steps %}
{% /tabitem %}
{% tabitem label="macOS" %}
  {% steps %}
  1. Open Terminal, type `bash <(curl -Ls https://bates64.com/setup-dx.sh)`, and press enter.
  2. Follow the instructions in the terminal window.
  {% /steps %}
{% /tabitem %}
{% tabitem label="Linux" %}
  {% steps %}
  1. Open a terminal and run `bash <(curl -Ls https://bates64.com/setup-dx.sh)`.
  2. Follow the instructions in the terminal window.
  {% /steps %}
{% /tabitem %}
{% /tabs %}

When the script finishes successfully, it should open the project in Visual Studio Code.

## Build and run

With Visual Studio Code focused, **press Ctrl+Shift+B (Cmd+Shift+B on macOS) to build the game.**

DX will automatically try to run the game in a known emulator after building. We recommend using the accurate emulator [ares](https://ares-emu.net). If you don't regularly test with ares and/or real hardware, your mod may not work correctly for others.

If DX did not find your emulator, you can load the ROM manually. The output ROM is located at `ver/us/build/papermario.z64`.

If you prefer real hardware, you can copy the output ROM `ver/us/build/papermario.z64` to a flashcart.

## Troubleshooting

If you run into any issues, you can ask for help in the `#papermario-dx` channel in the Star Haven Discord.

### I closed VSCode! How do I open it again?

You can reopen it by using the 'Recent' menu on the VSCode Welcome screen.

If you can't find it, you can open VSCode from a terminal. Open a terminal and run `code ~/papermario-dx`. Note that you should use WSL if you're on Windows.
